data.title: Collier Memorial State Park - Chiloquin OR
data.meta_description: Find AAA approved attractions and other local gems across North America. Learn more about Collier Memorial State Park or other things to do in Chiloquin.
data.text:
AAA Editor Notes

Collier Memorial State Park is at 46000 US 97N. The open-air museum is one of the largest collections of logging artifacts in the nation. Also on the grounds is a pioneer log-cabin village and a 1.5-mile hiking trail.

Pet friendly (call for restrictions/fees.). Camping is permitted. Picnicking is permitted.
